---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import MobileInstallNotice from "../components/MobileInstallNotice.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Fair Copy" description="Fair Copy strips formatting noise from Word documents while preserving emphasis and alignment.">
  <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-6">Black Letter Studio / Fair Copy</p>

  <h1 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-4xl leading-none tracking-tight mb-8">
    Fair <em class="text-oxblood not-italic font-normal">Copy.</em>
  </h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-12">
    Open a Word document. Click one button. Font faces, font sizes, colors, highlighting, comments, and sloppy indents — gone. Bold, italic, underline, and your paragraph alignment — kept. Now you have a clean document you can send, file, or format to house style.
  </p>

  <section class="py-8 border-y border-black/10 my-8 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">What Fair Copy keeps</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm text-ink-soft space-y-2">
        <li>&#x2713; Bold / italic / underline emphasis</li>
        <li>&#x2713; Paragraph alignment</li>
        <li>&#x2713; List structure (with normalized bullets)</li>
        <li>&#x2713; Tables (normalized borders)</li>
        <li>&#x2713; Footnotes and endnotes</li>
        <li>&#x2713; Hyperlinks (link preserved, formatting stripped)</li>
        <li>&#x2713; Section and page breaks</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">What Fair Copy removes</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm text-ink-soft space-y-2">
        <li>&#x2717; Font face / size / color variations</li>
        <li>&#x2717; Highlighting (configurable)</li>
        <li>&#x2717; Comments</li>
        <li>&#x2717; Custom indents and stray tab stops</li>
        <li>&#x2717; Inconsistent line and paragraph spacing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">Safe by default</h3>
    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-4">
      Three operations always surface a confirmation dialog &mdash; never silent, never surprising:
    </p>
    <ul class="text-ink-soft space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Tracked changes.</strong> Default is &ldquo;reject all&rdquo; &mdash; but only after you confirm, with options to review first or leave them alone.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Images.</strong> Default is &ldquo;warn and list&rdquo; &mdash; Fair Copy shows the images it found (signature blocks, letterheads, exhibits) and asks what to do.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Marked-Final or password-protected documents.</strong> Warned before any change.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8 border-t border-black/10">
    <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">Privacy</h3>
    <p class="text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mb-2">Fair Copy runs entirely inside Microsoft Word on your device. No cloud processing. No document content leaves your computer. The only network call Fair Copy makes during normal use is a one-time license activation against our own server (<code class="font-mono text-sm">fair-copy.blackletter.studio</code>) when you first redeem a code. After that, license tokens verify locally &mdash; Fair Copy works offline.</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft"><a href="/trust" class="text-oxblood underline">Full network-traffic inventory &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 border-t border-black/10">
    <MobileInstallNotice subject="Install Fair Copy when I'm at my desktop" shareUrl="https://blackletter.studio/fair-copy" />

    <div class="hidden md:block bg-paper border border-oxblood/30 rounded-md p-8 max-w-xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-oxblood mb-3">Install</p>
      <p class="font-display text-3xl mb-2"><strong class="font-normal">$49</strong> <span class="text-ink-soft text-lg">one-time</span></p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft mb-6">Lifetime license. First 5 documents free. No subscription, no account, no telemetry. License tokens verify locally &mdash; Fair Copy keeps working even if Black Letter goes dark.</p>

      <a href="/fair-copy/install" class="inline-block bg-ink text-paper px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-oxblood transition-colors">
        Add to Word &rarr;
      </a>
      <p class="text-xs text-ink-soft mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        Four-step sideload walkthrough. Works in Word for Mac, Windows, Web, and iPad.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xs text-ink-soft/80 mt-5 italic leading-relaxed border-t border-oxblood/20 pt-4">
        Early access: request a license code at <a href="mailto:hello@blackletter.studio?subject=Fair%20Copy%20early%20access" class="text-oxblood underline not-italic">hello@blackletter.studio</a>. Checkout and the Microsoft AppSource listing are in review &mdash; both paths serve the same add-in.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
